summary.para: This class is available in Office 2007 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is c:ser.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
**ser (Scatter Chart Series)**
This element specifies a series on a scatter chart.
|Parent Elements| |---------------------| |scatterChart (§21.2.2.161)|
|Child Elements|Subclause| |--------------------|---------------| |dLbls (Data Labels)|§21.2.2.49| |dPt (Data Point)|§21.2.2.52| |errBars (Error Bars)|§21.2.2.55| |extLst (Chart Extensibility)|§21.2.2.64| |idx (Index)|§21.2.2.84| |marker (Marker)|§21.2.2.106| |order (Order)|§21.2.2.128| |smooth (Smoothing)|§21.2.2.194| |spPr (Shape Properties)|§21.2.2.197| |trendline (Trendlines)|§21.2.2.211| |tx (Series Text)|§21.2.2.215| |xVal (X Values)|§21.2.2.234| |yVal (Y Values)|§21.2.2.237|
[*Note*: The W3C XML Schema definition of this element’s content model (CT_ScatterSer) is located in §A.5.1. *end note*]
[!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlcopyrightiso.md)]
